<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF13FF59A7ADFB55FDE5DAD6" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF13FF59A7ADFB55FEE9D8D5" blockId="138.[189,303,1210,1236]" box="[189,303,1210,1236]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF13FF59A7ADFB55FEE9D8D5" bold="true" box="[189,303,1210,1236]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF13FF59A7ADFB55FEE9D8D5" bold="true" box="[189,303,1210,1236]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF13FF59A7ADFB06FEB1DA26" blockId="138.[189,1401,1257,1575]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">
The 
<typeStatus id="D8511CC1FF13FF59A7E7FB06FE98D902" box="[247,350,1257,1283]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">holotype</typeStatus>
is small and very whitish, making it difficult to see details, and the opisthosoma is missing, but some characters could be observed. In the original description, Simon (1936) mentioned that 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF13FF59A7E0FADCFE40D94D" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1936" box="[240,390,1330,1357]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diblemma">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF13FF59A7E0FADCFE40D94D" box="[240,390,1330,1357]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">C. diblemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks lateral eyes, but small, whitish lateral eyes, were evident near the lateral margin of the carapace. The median eyes were also present. The sternum platelets were not yet formed. The cheliceral claw bears five teeth but it was impossible to observe teeth on the basal segment. Two dorsal spines and three ventral spines were evident on the pedipalp femur; three or four dorsal spines and two ventral spines were evident on the patella; and two dorsal spines on the tarsus. The tibia and tarsus of antenniform leg I comprise 21 and 37 articles, respectively. The basitibia of leg IV consists of three pseudo-articles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF13FF59A7ADF9BFFDE5DAD6" blockId="138.[188,1399,1616,1752]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">
The immaturity and poor preservation of the 
<typeStatus id="D8511CC1FF13FF59A5D4F9BFFCEDDA6B" box="[708,811,1616,1642]" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">holotype</typeStatus>
renders it impossible to form an opinion regarding the taxonomic validity of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF13FF59A6F9F99AFDB9DA8F" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1936" box="[489,639,1652,1679]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diblemma">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF13FF59A6F9F99AFDB9DA8F" box="[489,639,1652,1679]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">C. diblemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until such time as adults can be collected from the vicinity of the type locality. 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF13FF59A64AF976FDF4DAB5" author="Delle Cave L." box="[346,562,1689,1716]" firstAuthor="Delle Cave" journalOrPublisher="Redia" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="143 - 170" part="69" refId="ref147657" refString="Delle Cave L. 1986. Biospeleology of the Somaliland Amblypygi (Arachnida, Chelicerata) of the caves of the Showli Berdi and Mugdile (Bardera, Somaliland). Redia 69: 143 - 170." title="Biospeleology of the Somaliland Amblypygi (Arachnida, Chelicerata) of the caves of the Showli Berdi and Mugdile (Bardera, Somaliland)" type="journal article" year="1986">Delle Cave (1986)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF13FF59A5AEF976FC92DAB2" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1936" box="[702,852,1689,1715]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Charinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diblemma">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF13FF59A5AEF976FC92DAB2" box="[702,852,1689,1715]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="139">C. diblemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as nomen dubium, not by 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF13FF59A399F976FA95DAB2" author="Weygoldt P." box="[1161,1363,1689,1715]" editor="Juberthie C. &amp; Decu V." firstAuthor="Weygoldt" journalOrPublisher="Societe de Biospeologie, Moulis and Bucarest" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" pagination="241 - 247" refId="ref155707" refString="Weygoldt P. 1994. Amblypygi. In: Juberthie C. &amp; Decu V. (eds) Encyclopaedia Biospeologica: 241 - 247. Societe de Biospeologie, Moulis and Bucarest." title="Amblypygi" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Encyclopaedia Biospeologica" year="1994">Weygoldt (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, as stated in 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF13FF59A637F951FE0ADAD6" author="Harvey M. S." box="[295,460,1725,1752]" firstAuthor="Harvey" journalOrPublisher="CSIRO Publishing, Collingwood, Australia" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" refId="ref149587" refString="Harvey M. S. 2003. Catalogue of the Smaller Arachnid Orders of the World. Amblypygi, Uropygi, Schizomida, Palpigradi, Ricinulei and Solifugae. CSIRO Publishing, Collingwood, Australia. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / 9780643090071" title="Catalogue of the Smaller Arachnid Orders of the World. Amblypygi, Uropygi, Schizomida, Palpigradi, Ricinulei and Solifugae" type="book" year="2003">Harvey (2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="637BDF92FF13FF59A6C7F952FDD1DAD6" accessDate="2021-07-02" author="Harvey M. S." box="[471,535,1725,1751]" firstAuthor="Harvey" journalOrPublisher="Western Australian Museum, Perth" pageId="138" pageNumber="139" publicationUrl="http://museum.wa.gov.au/catalogues-beta/whip-spiders" refId="ref149633" refString="Harvey M. S. 2013. Whip Spiders of the World, version 1.0. Western Australian Museum, Perth. Available from http: // museum. wa. gov. au / catalogues-beta / whip-spiders [accessed 2 Jul. 2021]." title="Whip Spiders of the World, version 1.0" type="url" year="2013">2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
